    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbilityRenderer
    Renders visual effects for special abilities on the battlefield.
    AntiArmoredUnit
    A unit which can attack from close range and can deal a lot of damage to Armored Unit.
    ArmoredUnit
    A unit which can attack from close range and can reduce damage taken.
    Attackable
    Interface representing any entity that can take damage and has a life state.
    Base
    The base of the player for deploying Unit and setup Turret; if hp is 0 or less than 0, the game ends.
    BattlefieldView
    The primary view for the game battlefield.
    CurrencySystem
    The currency in-game for purchasing units, turrets or upgrades.
    DamagePopupRenderer
    Utility class for rendering floating damage text popups.
    EndGameView
    Represents the overlay view displayed when the game ends (Win or Lose).
    GameController
    Controller class that bridges the game logic (GameManager) and the user interface.
    GameManager
    The core logic engine for the game.
    GameManager.DamageEvent
     
    GameManager.GameState
     
    HUD
    The Heads-Up Display (HUD) containing game controls and status information.
    LongRangeTurret
    A specialized turret with extended range.
    Main
    The entry point of the Prasart Dang Battle application.
    MeleeUnit
    A unit which can attack from close range.
    MenuView
    Represents the main menu and tutorial screens of the application.
    NukeAbility
    The ability to nuke on opponent unit.
    Projectile
    Represents a projectile fired by a unit or turret in the game.
    ProjectileRenderer
    Renders projectiles on the battlefield.
    RangedUnit
    A unit which can attack from the long range.
    SceneManager
    Manages the transitions between different scenes in the JavaFX application.
    SoundManager
    Handles the loading and playback of all audio resources in the game.
    SpecialAbility
    An abstract class on special ability which player can choose to use.
    StandardTurret
    A basic turret with balanced stats.
    Turret
    Abstract base class for all defensive turrets.
    TurretRenderer
    Renders turrets on the battlefield using an ImageView.
    Unit
    The unit which will available to attack opponent units or base.
    UnitRenderer
    Renders units on the battlefield, including their sprite and health bar.
    UpgradeSystem
    Upgrading System for Unit Attack, Unit HP, Turret Attack, Turret Range and Turret Capacity.
